{{see|Cent}}
==English==
{{wikipedia}} 
===Etymology===
Borrowed from Old French ''cent'', “hundred”, from Latin [[centum]], from Proto-Indo-European ''*(d)ḱm̥tóm''.  

===Pronunciation===
{| border=1 cellpadding=5
| [[w:AHD|AHD]] || sĕnt
|-
| [[w:IPA|IPA]] || /sɛnt/
|-
| [[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] || /sEnt/
|}

====Homophones====
*[[scent]], [[sent]] [[Category:English homophones]]

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|Cent (currency)}}
{{en-noun}}

# A [[subunit]] of currency equal to [[one-hundredth]] of the main unit of currency in many countries, including the [[United States]].  Symbol: [[¢]].
# A [[subunit]] of currency equal to one-hundredth of the [[euro]].
# A coin having [[face value]] of one cent (in either of the above senses).

====Synonyms====
*(''of a dollar''): [[dollarcent]]
*(''of a euro''): [[eurocent]]
*(''coin''): (''Canada, US'') [[penny]]

