Old French ''cent'', "hundred", from Latin [[centum]], from Proto-Indo-European ''*(d)ḱm̥tóm''.  Formal cognates include Sanskrit [[शतं]], (śataṃ) [[शतम्]] (śatam), [[Old Church Slavonic]] [[съто]] (sŭto), and Old English [[hund]].

